
- KAFKA: central hub for sharing everything
- producer: an application that sends data to Kafka
- Consumer: an application that request & receive data from Kafka
- Broker:  Kafka server
- Cluster: Group of computers
- Topic:   A name for a Kafka stream
- Partition: Part of a topic (usually store on a seperate computer)
- Offset: Unique id for a message within a partiition
- Consumer groups: a group of consumers acting as a single logical unit


